liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: A good session for Australia, putting on their best opening stand of the series at last asking. Both Usman Khawaja and David Warner look solid out there, although the scoring slowed late in the session. Also looming is Mark Wood, who hasn't been called upon yet. Troublingly, the rain is falling and the pitch is being covered. It's supposed to get worse today too, which is ominous for fans of watching cricket over weather radars.

props.alt: Australia batter Usman Khawaja and England wicketkeeper Jonny Bairstow watch a ball go away from them after a shot.

children.content: A good session for Australia, putting on their best opening stand of the series at last asking.
Both Usman Khawaja and David Warner look solid out there, although the scoring slowed late in the session.
Also looming is Mark Wood, who hasn't been called upon yet.
Troublingly, the rain is falling and the pitch is being covered. It's supposed to get worse today too, which is ominous for fans of watching cricket over weather radars.
